<h3 id="overview">Overview</h3>
<p>
    Horizontal <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/disclosure/examples/disclosure-navigation/">APG
    Disclosure Navigation</a> header: a row of section heads, each a
    <code>&lt;button aria-expanded aria-controls&gt;</code> disclosing an absolutely-positioned dropdown
    panel of links below it. Below the 940px breakpoint the row collapses to an inline accordion. It is the
    horizontal-popup counterpart of the vertical <a href="/blocks/sectioned-nav/">sectioned-nav</a> — the same
    disclosure pattern, the other orientation — and it reproduces the WE-docs site nav.
</p>
<p>
    Reveal is CSS on <code>:hover</code>; the keyboard/click path is wired imperatively (the mode&nbsp;C
    convention — no behavior registry in-document): click / <kbd>Enter</kbd> / <kbd>Space</kbd> toggles a
    section (opening one closes its siblings), <kbd>Escape</kbd> collapses the open section and returns focus
    to its head, and an outside click or focus dismisses any open panel. The link for the current page carries
    <code>aria-current="page"</code>.
</p>
<p>
    Built for <a href="/backlog/931-dogfooded-fui-docs-chrome-renders-broken-fix-it-to-a-correct/">#931</a>
    so the WE-docs chrome dogfood (<a href="/backlog/865-migrate-we-docs-site-chrome-to-fui-components-header-nav-foo/">#865</a>)
    renders a compact horizontal header — mounted in the header bar of the
    <a href="/blocks/app-shell/">app-shell</a> via the in-document (mode&nbsp;C) embed path.
</p>

<h3 id="usage">Usage</h3>
{% highlight "typescript" %}
import { mountDisclosureNav } from '@frontierui/blocks/disclosure-nav';

mountDisclosureNav(shadowRoot, {
  ariaLabel: 'Main',
  sections: [
    { id: 'standards', label: 'Standards', links: [
      { href: '/intents/', label: 'Intents' },
      { href: '/blocks/', label: 'Blocks', current: true },
      { href: '/protocols/', label: 'Protocols' },
    ] },
    { id: 'explore', label: 'Explore', links: [
      { href: '/demos/', label: 'Demos' },
      { href: '/backlog/', label: 'Backlog' },
    ] },
  ],
});
{% endhighlight %}

<h3 id="exports">Exports</h3>
<ul>
    <li><code>createDisclosureNav(config)</code> — builds the <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> element and wires the disclosure behavior</li>
    <li><code>mountDisclosureNav(root, config)</code> — mounts into a shadow root, returns a teardown fn</li>
    <li><code>mountInDocument(root)</code> — the mode-C contract entry point (default config)</li>
</ul>
